I

Implies - Annotation Interface in org.jspecify.meta
Indicates that an annotation type conveys all of the same meaning as the given annotation type(s); for example, @Implies(One.class) @interface Two {} says that any usage of @Two implicitly conveys all the same meaning as @One (with no attributes) would in the same location.

N

NonNull - Annotation Interface in org.jspecify.nullness
Indicates that the annotated type usage is considered to exclude null as a value; rarely needed within null-marked code.
Nullable - Annotation Interface in org.jspecify.nullness
Indicates that the annotated type usage (commonly a variable type or return type) is considered to include null as a value.
NullMarked - Annotation Interface in org.jspecify.nullness
Indicates that the annotated element and the code transitively enclosed within it are null-marked code: there, type usages are generally considered to exclude null as a value unless specified otherwise.
NullUnmarked - Annotation Interface in org.jspecify.nullness
Indicates that the annotated element and the code transitively enclosed within it is null-unmarked code: there, type usages generally have unspecified nullness unless explicitly annotated otherwise.

O

org.jspecify.meta - package org.jspecify.meta
Annotations addressing cross-cutting concerns among other annotation types.
org.jspecify.nullness - package org.jspecify.nullness
The primary annotations of interest in this package are NullMarked and Nullable.

V

value() - Element in annotation interface org.jspecify.meta.Implies
The annotation types implied by this annotation type (the one that is itself annotated with Implies).
